        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 6.  UNDERTUTOR
Art. 4201.  Appointment; oath
At the time judgment is rendered appointing a tutor, the court shall also appoint a responsible person as undertutor.
Before entering upon the performance of his official duties, the undertutor must take an oath to discharge faithfully the duties of his office.</p>
        </content>
